# PCG Best Practices

When working on PCG (Procedural Content Generation) graphs, volumes, or spawners:

1. **Before changing the PCG graph or adding nodes:** Read [docs/PCG_BEST_PRACTICES.md](docs/PCG_BEST_PRACTICES.md) and [docs/PCG_VARIABLES_NO_ACCESS.md](docs/PCG_VARIABLES_NO_ACCESS.md). The former describes the minimal working graph, mandatory manual steps, and when to use Partitioned/Hierarchical generation; the latter lists settings that automation cannot set and must be done in the Editor.

2. **When the user reports "Generate produces nothing":** Follow [docs/PCG_SETUP.md](docs/PCG_SETUP.md) section "Generate produces nothing (checklist)" and use the **pcg-validate** skill (ordered checklist, Output Log, Surface Sampler Debug). Do not suggest graph changes before verifying Get Landscape Data, mesh list, graph assignment, Landscape tag, and World Partition Load All.

3. **When suggesting new PCG nodes or graph structure:** Ensure the proposal aligns with the minimal working graph (Get Landscape Data → Surface Sampler → Static Mesh Spawner) and document which steps remain manual per PCG_VARIABLES_NO_ACCESS.
